  <body>
    <segment id="1">
Last bastion
</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="27" relname="joint">


Americans would probably throw themselves on the floor and laugh out loud at this question:
</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="26" relname="span">  

Smoking in a city hall,
</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="9" relname="e-elaboration"> 

where children and adolescents are regularly exercising and breathing heavily?
</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="28" relname="span">  

The mere thought of it would be unthinkable in a country where smoking in public buildings, airports, and even in restaurants (even at tables outdoors in the middle of Manhattan!) is punishable by law.
</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="23" relname="preparation">  

And Germany?
</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="23" relname="conjunction"> 

Uninhibited smoking and puffing everywhere,
</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="22" relname="span"> 


and often a non-smoker is even met with aggression,
</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="5" relname="condition"> 


when he kindly points out that it smells unbearably...
</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="25" relname="span">  

In this respect, the persistence with which the Falkensee city administration did not grant a concert permit to a Berlin music group for the city hall - essentially one of the last smoke-free bastions - is to be commended.
</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="17" relname="preparation">  

Even if it may sound exaggerated
</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="16" relname="condition">  

Anyone who seriously talks about youth protection (keyword addiction risks) 
</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="16" relname="span"> 

should not send small people to a place for floor gymnastics 
</segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="14" relname="e-elaboration"> 

where it smells like in a pub the morning after the Christmas party.
</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="18" relname="cause">  

This principle is rightly so important to the responsible authorities 
</segment>
    <segment id="18" parent="19" relname="span"> 

that they are not willing to sell it for a few marks of hall rental.
</segment>
<group id="16" type="span" parent="17" relname="span" />
